This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category as it proposes a method for structure learning of pairwise Markov random fields (MRFs) using an incremental approach. The paper also mentions the use of heuristics and optimization techniques, which are common in the machine learning field. Additionally, the paper could also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) categories as MRFs are commonly used in these fields. The use of reservoir sampling and search history could also suggest that this paper could be relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) category. Finally, the paper's focus on efficiency and speedup could also make it relevant to the social and information networks (cs.SI) category.
